snippet.title: Building with Gemini 3, AI Studio, Antigravity, and Nano Banana | The Agent Factory Podcast
snippet.description:
Gemini 3 is here, and it is evolving the way developers build. In this episode of The Agent Factory, host Amit Maraj sits down with Paige Bailey from Google DeepMind to break down the latest rapid fire releases from Google, including the highly anticipated Gemini 3 Pro, Nano Banana Pro, and the new AI-native IDE, Antigravity.

Gemini 3 represents a massive leap forward, moving from multimodal understanding (Gemini 1) and reasoning (Gemini 2) to genuine agency and acting. It excels at coding, tool use, and long range planningâ€”as evidenced by its strong performance on a variety of agentic benchmarks.

Listen along as Paige builds "Nordic Shield"â€”a multimodal insurance cataloging agentâ€”live in Google AI Studio using the new build feature and Gemini Live. As a bonus, Amit demonstrates how to use the Antigravity IDE to redesign a website using nothing but screenshots and Gemini 3â€™s multimodal capabilities.

Chapters:
00:00 - Intro & welcome Paige Bailey 
00:42 - Google's new AI releases 
02:49 - What is Gemini 3? (The evolution from 1.0) 
06:48 - The "Vending Bench": AI running a business 
11:21 - Demo: Building "Nordic Shield" in AI studio 
18:15 - Debugging & "Auto-Fix" in action 
21:40 - Using the annotate feature for UI design 
25:17 - Gemini Live & Google Search grounding 
28:34 - Nano Banana Pro: State of the art Image Gen 
30:27 - Demo: Website redesign with Antigravity IDE 
35:41 - The full Google AI stack
